        <skos:scopeNote xml:lang="en">Originally denoting a Byzantine vessel, powered by oars, from the 6th century onwards, this developed into a large Mediterranean ship with oars and a single mast, used for trade or for war transport, (e.g. during the Crusades) until the 15th century.</skos:scopeNote>
        <skos:inScheme rdf:resource="http://purl.org/heritagedata/schemes/eh_tmc"/>
