  <skos:Concept rdf:about="http://purl.org/heritagedata/schemes/eh_tmc/concepts/100384">
    <skos:scopeNote xml:lang="en">A boat specifically designed for saving lives at sea, they can be either: a boat carried on a larger vessel for use in emergency evacuation of crew and passengers in the event of shipwreck or a boat built for the purpose of shore-to-sea rescue missions.</skos:scopeNote>
