    <skos:prefLabel xml:lang="en">Sewn Boat</skos:prefLabel>
    <skos:scopeNote xml:lang="en">A type of clinker built wooden boat or ship held together with tendons of flexible wood such as roots and willow branches. Sewn boat construction techniques were used in many parts of the world prior to the development of metal fasteners.</skos:scopeNote>
